---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Pavement Maintenance Case Studies | Asphalt Repair Results"
  description="See field results for Shining Road Technology crack sealing, cold mix asphalt, production plants, and pavement maintenance projects worldwide."
>
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-3">Case Studies</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-500 mb-12">Real-world results with our pavement maintenance products</p>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <!-- Case 1 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <div class="p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
              <span class="text-xs font-medium text-primary bg-blue-50 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Crack Sealing</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-400">Highway Project</span>
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Municipal Highway Crack Sealing — 120 km, Southeast Asia</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-6">
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Project Scale</div>
                <div class="font-semibold">120 lane-km</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Product Used</div>
                <div class="font-semibold">Hot-applied sealant (ASTM D6690 Type II)</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Result</div>
                <div class="font-semibold text-green-600">95% seal intact after 24 months</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
              A provincial highway authority in Southeast Asia selected our hot-applied crack sealant for a 120 km preventive maintenance program on their busiest arterial route. The route carries 15,000+ vehicles/day with a high percentage of heavy trucks.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              After 24 months of service including two monsoon seasons, independent inspection showed 95% of seals remained intact — significantly outperforming the previously used local product which averaged 70% retention over the same period. The authority has since adopted our product as their standard specification.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Case 2 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <div class="p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
              <span class="text-xs font-medium text-amber-600 bg-amber-50 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Cold Mix Asphalt</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-400">Airport Maintenance</span>
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Airport Taxiway Emergency Repairs — Middle East</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-6">
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Project Type</div>
                <div class="font-semibold">Night-time emergency pothole repairs</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Product Used</div>
                <div class="font-semibold">Cold mix asphalt (permanent grade, 0–10 mm)</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Key Metric</div>
                <div class="font-semibold text-green-600">Repairs completed in 4-hour window — 3× faster than hot mix</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
              An international airport in the Middle East needed to repair potholes on an active taxiway during a 4-hour nightly closure window. Hot mix was impractical — the nearest plant was 90 minutes away and the minimum order was uneconomical for small patch quantities.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Using our cold mix asphalt stored on-site, the maintenance crew completed all repairs within the closure window, compacted with a small vibratory roller, and reopened to aircraft traffic immediately. Six months later, all patches remained intact with no FOD (foreign object debris) incidents reported.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Case 3 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <div class="p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
              <span class="text-xs font-medium text-green-600 bg-green-50 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Production Plant</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-400">Technology Transfer</span>
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Cold Mix Plant + Technology License — East Africa</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-6">
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Scope</div>
                <div class="font-semibold">30 TPH plant + full technology license</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Timeline</div>
                <div class="font-semibold">6 months contract to production</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Outcome</div>
                <div class="font-semibold text-green-600">First local cold mix manufacturer in country</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
              A major East African construction materials supplier partnered with us to establish the country's first domestic cold mix asphalt production capability. Previously, all cold mix was imported at high cost with long lead times.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              We delivered a complete 30 TPH production plant with 5 proprietary formulations adapted for local aggregates and climate. Our engineers provided 2 weeks of on-site training for 6 operators and QC staff. The partner achieved commercial production within 6 months of contract signing and is now supplying government road agencies, mining operations, and municipal contractors — at 40% lower cost than imported alternatives.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Case 4 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <div class="p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
              <span class="text-xs font-medium text-purple-600 bg-purple-50 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Emulsified Asphalt</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-400">Chip Seal Program</span>
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Rural Road Chip Seal Program — South America</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-6">
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Project Scale</div>
                <div class="font-semibold">450 km rural road network</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Product Used</div>
                <div class="font-semibold">CRS-2 cationic rapid-set emulsion</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Result</div>
                <div class="font-semibold text-green-600">60% cost savings vs. hot mix overlay</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
              A South American state road agency needed to preserve 450 km of rural roads with limited budget. Hot mix overlay was cost-prohibitive at $25/m². Our technical team recommended a double chip seal treatment using CRS-2 emulsion — total cost approximately $10/m² including aggregate.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Three years post-application, the chip seal sections show excellent aggregate retention and skid resistance with minimal maintenance required. The agency has expanded the program to an additional 800 km.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="text-center mt-12 bg-primary text-white rounded-2xl p-10">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Have a Similar Project?</h3>
        <p class="text-blue-100 mb-6 max-w-md mx-auto">Tell us about your pavement maintenance challenge — we'll recommend the right product and approach.</p>
        <a href="/contact/" class="inline-flex items-center px-8 py-3 bg-white text-primary font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors">
          Contact Our Technical Team
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
